.Dd January 06, 2026
.Dt sfreport 8
.Os Linux
.Sh NAME
.Nm sfreport
.Nd diagnostics tool for AMD Solarflare hardware and software
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Ar filename
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is an diagnostics tool for Linux systems running
AMD Solarflare branded hardware and software.
.Pp
This Perl script generates an HTML file.
You may specify an alternate file name on the command line.
If the file name does not end in
.Dq .htm
or
.Dq .html
the information will be written in plain text format.
.Pp
The generated file contains information about the configuration of the
AMD Solarflare NIC and the system it is installed in.
.Pp
For example:
.Bl -bullet -compact
.It
Interface statistics such as packet drops
.It
AMD-Solarflare specific driver logging/error messages
.It
Firmware and driver settings + version information
.It
AMD-Solarflare product information such as NIC model
.It
System information such as CPU architechture, kernel and OS
.El
This information is intended for use by AMD Solarflare engineers but is recorded in a text format that may be useful to others.
.Ss Usage
For the collection of full diagnostics information, the
.Nm
script should be run with superuser permissions.
.Pp
For example:
.Pp
$ sudo
.Nm
.Pp
The output of
.Nm
will be in html format.
.Pp
The default filename will be in the format
.Pa sfreport-'hostname'-'date'-'time'.html
and will be written to the current directory.
.Ss Notes
Information is collected using standard Linux utilites such as
.Xr ethtool 8
or
.Xr cat 1 .
For example,
.Sq Interface Statistics
are gathered using
.Ic ethtool -S
.Pp
.Nm
runs a series of Linux commands that are selected to be suitable to run on production systems.
These read information, without changing any settings.
However, there may be a performance impact while these commands are being run.
